Perform portfolio analysis to identify potential credit risks and provide professional advice on risk mitigation. Gather and analyse market information, monitor the performance of credit facilities utilization to identify early signs of credit deterioration. Perform impairment assessment, conduct procedural reviews and relevant MIS reports. Make recommendations and review on credit risk management strategies to comply with relevant regulatory requirements.

Requirements:

Degree holder in Risk Management, Finance, Economics, Accounting, Information System or related disciplines;
At least 3 years experience in credit risk management and monitoring;
Sound knowledge in legal and regulatory requirements, Basel III and banking practices on credit risk management;
Hands-on experience of MS Excel, PowerPoint (Knowledge in database management and statistical computer applications is an advantage);
Analytical, independent with good communication skills;
Proficient in both spoken and written English and Chinese.

(Candidate with less experience will be considered as Assistant Credit Monitoring Manager.)

