As our Senior Officer/ Assistant Manager, Risk Management & Credit Control, you will be leading a team to monitor, analyze, and manage credit risks in our equities and derivatives trading business. Responsibilities include but not limited to:

Monitor daily trading activities to ensure all activities are complied with the Company’s credit risk management policies & guidelines and external regulatory requirements;
Monitor daily market movements; identify market & liquidity risk exposures and promptly submit escalation report of any irregularities and limit excesses;
Review, assess, and approve credit facility & trading limits applications;
Monitor the credit risks of margin financing portfolios, and ensure margin control actions & procedures are performed in a timely fashion;
Conduct simulations and stress testing on selected risk factors/ investment portfolios on regular and ad-hoc basis;
Review and assess product risk;
Identify possible operational risks and provide recommendations to address the control weakness
Keep abreast of latest rules and regulations related to credit risk management; review, update, and revise risk management guidelines, policies, and procedures on a timely basis;
Prepare daily and monthly credit risk analysis reports to management;
Assist in other ad-hoc projects as assigned.

Requirements:

Degree holder in Risk Management, Finance or related disciplines;
At least 3 years of solid risk management and credit control experiences in securities firms with field experience in handling different asset classes trading across multiple markets
Solid experiences in credit/margin control with SFC RA1 license is an  advantage; In-depth understanding of legal and regulatory requirements on credit risk management;
Conscious thought in compliance and control
Strong analytical, numerical, report writing and problem solving skills;
Knowledge in market risk system, such as Bloomberg, Reuters;
Excellent interpersonal, communication and negotiation skills;
Experience in leading a small team in risk management and credit control
Advanced level on Excel VBA and Access or other statistics software;
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese (Cantonese & Putonghua).
Candidates with more experience would be considered as Assistant Manager, RMC.

Please apply in confidence with full resume, current and expected salary in the subject line to the Human Resources Department, CASH Financial Services Group Limited, 22/F, Manhattan Place, 23 Wang Tai Road, Kowloon Bay, Hong Kong.

Responsibilities:
Assist supervisor in leading and managing the credit risk modeling and credit analytics team;
Maintain credit rating models for measurement and management of credit risk for the Bank’s portfolio;
Liaise with different units to formulate credit MIS processes, support stress testing of regulatory capital, data management projects and implementation of new initiatives such as IFRS9, BELR, ICAAP, and SA-CCR;
Manage the credit portfolio reporting and the associated MIS; and
Perform other ad hoc projects or assignments.
Requirements:
University graduate in Finance, Economics, Accounting, Risk Management, Statistics or related disciplines;
CFA, Accountant and/or FRM is a plus; and HKIB ECF-CRM preferable;
Minimum of 7 years’ solid bank experience in credit risk management; project management experience is a plus;
Expansive knowledge of credit risk requirement and credit policy; and familiar with credit risk stress testing, IFRS9, ICAAP and SA-CCR rating models (PD) and LGD/EAD measurement;
Strong self-motivation and creativity, with excellent communication and analytical skills;
Demonstrated ability to rapidly build relationships with key stakeholders; and
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Vice President.
