Responsibilities:

Assist CCO to lead a team of credit analyst to conduct credit analysis and underwriting on new potential clients and regular review of existing clients, preparation of credit underwriting reports on a timely basis with minimal supervision and ensure timely reporting of related credit information and reports of subordinates;
Formulate and review Risk Framework, Credit Policy, development and enhancement of adequate credit underwriting procedures;
Assist Risk Management to conduct portfolio risk management and to ensure effective risk monitoring and special assets management, including early warning mechanisms, contingency and debt collection plans;
Conduct fraud prevention measurements to ensure the underlying assets of the Trade Finance Projects are of good credit quality;
To participate in project development and liaise with different department;
Assist to implement automation of credit underwriting procedures;
Perform other ad-hoc tasks and assist in daily operation.

Requirements:

University degree or high diploma in Finance, Accounting, Banking, Risk Management or related discipline;
At least 5 to 8 year experience in credit analysis earned from banking or finance sector;
Knowledge in Trade Finance with experience in E-commerce industry will be an advantage
Fluent in both spoken and written English and Chinese (Cantonese and Mandarin a plus);
A team player with strong interpersonal and relationship building skills with internal and external business partners;
Self-motivated, proactive and results oriented;
Able to work in a fast-paced start-up environment, with multi-tasking and keen to details;
Being creative and tech-savvy on new apps development and new solutions, can think outside the box for better solutions.

Our client is a well-established MNC bank and recently seeking a flexible candidate for the Corporate Loan - Senior Officer position to join their newly expanded branch. 

Responsibilities:

Perform Syndication Agency function and loan administration as an officer; 
Review structured & syndicated loan documentation drafts, and to ensure all terms and conditions are align with the bank’s policy.
To work closely with internal and external parties for loan draw down and credit administration work;
Perform customer due diligent (KYC);
Monitor & follow up documentation deficiency and outstanding loan documents;
Requirements:

Degree holder or above
Self-motivating, flexible and can-do attitude preferred
At least 3 years’ experience in credit process / monitoring of Corporate Banking industry
Proficient in English

Global Banking Division – Financial Institutions Group

Hang Seng's Global Banking business provides a broad spectrum of financing solutions to large corporations and financial institutions. As a strategic financial partner to corporate customers, Hang Seng offers a comprehensive range of products and services including bilateral and syndication loans, project financing, property development financing, property investment loans, working capital financing, trade financing, cash management and treasury products. Our experienced and knowledgeable professionals understand the specific requirements of our customers and are committed to providing tailor-made financial packages in their best interests.

We are currently seeking a high caliber professional to join our department as Assistant Business and Credit Control Manager.
Principal responsibilities
To support the business and credit control of the department with particular focus on the following aspects:
Monitor credit limit utilization to ensure that irregularities are properly controlled;
Support team head to implement compliance policy and procedures to ensure the business and systems are compliant;
Prepare various reports as required by the Group / regulatory authorities as well as review the credit procedures and control measures to ensure compliance with the Bank’s credit policy;
Participate in the development, maintenance and enhancement of management information system as well as other ad hoc projects;
Oversee the general administrative function of the department
Requirements
University degree in Business Administration, Finance, Accounting OR other relevant professional qualifications;
Minimum of two years' relevant experience in credit control, risk management, accounting or management information system;
Sound knowledge of application software;
Strong numerical aptitude, with good communication and analytical skills;
Proficiency in both English and Chinese;
Great sense of ownership and servicing mindset to ensure efficient and effective customer service processes
If you would like to explore other opportunities at Hang Seng Hong Kong, please visit www.hangseng.com/careers/ for details.

